    <div class="example" id="while">
      <h2><a href="./">Lua by Example</a>: While</h2>
      
      <table>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>Can be used much like a <code>for</code> loop</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
            
          <pre class="chroma">
<span class="kd">local</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">1</span>
<span class="kr">while</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="mi">5</span> <span class="kr">do</span>
    <span class="n">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span>
<span class="kr">end</span></pre>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>Common use of a <code>while</code> loop is an infinite loop.
<code>break</code> can be used to end the loop early</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code">
            
          <pre class="chroma">
<span class="kr">while</span> <span class="kc">true</span> <span class="kr">do</span>
   <span class="n">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;This loop will run forever.&#34;</span><span class="p">)</span>
   <span class="kr">break</span>
<span class="kr">end</span></pre>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
      </table>
      
      <table>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            
          </td>
          <td class="code">
            
          <pre class="chroma"><span class="gp">$</span> lua while.lua</pre>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
      </table>
      
      
